# Statistik Pengunjung Perpustakaan Daerah "Cerdas Bangsa"

|------------------|-------------------------------|----------------------------|-----------------------|-------------------------------------------|
| Senin            | 155                           | 62                         | 41                    | 258                                       |
| Selasa           | 148                           | 58                         | 38                    | 244                                       |
| Rabu             | 152                           | 61                         | 42                    | 255                                       |
| Kamis            | 160                           | 65                         | 45                    | 270                                       |

*Tabel P1. Data pengunjung merupakan rata-rata dari kategori pengunjung pagi, siang, dan sore per hari operasional.*

## Analisis Aktivitas Peminjaman Buku (April 2025)

| Jenis Buku Populer | Total Peminjaman (eksemplar) | Tingkat Pengembalian Tepat Waktu (%) | Total Denda Keterlambatan (Rp) | Rekomendasi Program Literasi                      |

| Referensi Studi    | 153                          | 98.0%                                | 28,500                         | Perpanjang jam buka area referensi saat ujian.    |

# Restaurant Health Inspection Scores - City of Metroville

Department of Health - Inspection Cycle: Q1 2025 (January - March)

Summary of health inspection scores for licensed food establishments, categorized by lead inspector for trend analysis.

## Inspection Results for High Volume Establishments by Lead Inspector

| Lead Inspector ID | Avg. Score (out of 100) | Avg. Critical Violations per Inspection | Avg. Non-Critical Violations per Inspection | % Establishments Requiring Follow-up | Establishments Inspected | Key Violation Focus Area Observed |
|-------------------|-------------------------|-------------------------------------------|---------------------------------------------|----------------------------------------|--------------------------|-----------------------------------|
| Insp_A71          | 91.5                    | 0.2                                       | 3.5                                         | 15%                                    | 20                       | Minor cleaning, signage           |
| Insp_B34          | 79.0                    | 0.8                                       | 5.2                                         | 45%                                    | 22                       | Food temperature, handwashing     |
| Insp_C90          | 86.2                    | 0.1                                       | 6.8 (documentation heavy)                 | 25%                                    | 18                       | Labeling, record keeping          |
*Table HS1. Inspection outcomes represent averages for establishments visited by each lead inspector in Q1 2025. Specific scores: EST-00123 (92), EST-00456 (78), EST-00789 (85), EST-01011 (65).*

## Violation Type Frequency and Corrective Action Analysis (Q1 2025)

| Violation Category             | Total Instances Q1 | Common Locations of Violation      | Recommended Corrective Action Emphasis                                  | % Re-occurrence from Previous Qtr |
|--------------------------------|--------------------|------------------------------------|-------------------------------------------------------------------------|-----------------------------------|
| Improper Food Holding Temps    | 16                 | Buffet lines, Cold prep stations   | Mandatory staff retraining on temp logs & equipment calibration.        | 12%                               |
| Poor Personal Hygiene Practices| 11                 | Kitchen staff, Food handlers       | Reinforce handwashing protocols, glove use, and illness reporting.      | 8%                                |
| Pest Infestation Evidence      | 6                  | Storage areas, Kitchen perimeters  | Immediate professional pest control; seal entry points.                 | 3% (Urgent Follow-up)             |
| Cross-Contamination Risks      | 9                  | Cutting boards, Utensils, Prep areas| Color-coded systems, separate prep zones, sanitizer availability.       | 5%                                |
| Improper Chemical Storage      | 4                  | Near food prep, Unlabeled containers| Designated storage, clear labeling, MSDS accessible.                    | 2%                                |

**Key Directives:** Increased focus on temperature control and pest prevention for establishments inspected by Insp_B34. All establishments receiving scores below 80 require mandatory re-inspection within 30 days. Public disclosure of scores above 90 will be highlighted on the city website.

# Public Park Amenities Usage & Condition Report - Spring 2025

City Parks & Recreation Department - Metro City Parks

Assessment of public park amenity usage frequency and current condition to guide maintenance schedules and budget allocation for improvements.

## Amenity Usage Frequency and Reported Issues by Monitored Park (Spring 2025 Average Weekly Observations)

| Monitored Park Name | Playground Usage (High/Med/Low) | Sports Court Usage (H/M/L) | Picnic Area Usage (H/M/L) | Walking Trail Usage (H/M/L) | Total Reported Issues (Count this period) | Priority Maintenance Needs                     |
|---------------------|---------------------------------|------------------------------|-----------------------------|-----------------------------|-------------------------------------------|------------------------------------------------|
| Liberty_Gardens     | High (260 obs)                  | High (185 obs)               | High (310 obs)              | High (455 obs)              | 10                                        | Trash overflow (picnic), minor playground wear |
| Willow_Creek_Park   | Medium (125 obs)                | Medium (92 obs)              | Medium (155 obs)            | High (350 obs)              | 6                                         | Path erosion (trails), one broken basketball net|
| Northwood_Commons   | High (245 obs)                  | Medium (85 obs)              | High (290 obs)              | Medium (210 obs)            | 7                                         | General wear on play structures, some litter   |
| Southside_Green     | Low (35 obs)                    | Low (22 obs)                 | Medium (80 obs)             | Low (85 obs)                | 2                                         | Underutilized, needs promotion/new features    |
*Table AU1. Usage data based on weekly observational counts and issue reports logged via park maintenance system.*

## Amenity Condition Ratings and Maintenance Schedule (Spring 2025)

| Amenity Category          | Overall Average Condition Rating (1=Poor, 5=Excellent) | Last General Inspection Date | Next Major Maintenance / Upgrade Scheduled             | Budget Allocation Priority (High/Med/Low) | Notes on Condition                                 |
|---------------------------|--------------------------------------------------------|------------------------------|--------------------------------------------------------|-------------------------------------------|----------------------------------------------------|
| Playground Structures     | 3.75                                                   | March 2025                   | Q3 2025 (Safety surfacing & some component replacements)| High                                      | Some parks show more wear; Northwood needs attention.|
| Sports Court Surfaces     | 3.15                                                   | February 2025                | Q4 2025 (Resurfacing for Willow Creek & Liberty)       | High                                      | Cracks appearing, nets need frequent replacement.    |
| Benches, Tables, & Grills | 3.95                                                   | April 2025                   | Ongoing (as needed repairs & replacements)             | Medium                                    | Generally good, some graffiti issues at Liberty.   |
| Pathway & Trail Conditions| 3.45                                                   | March 2025                   | Q3 2025 (Erosion control & minor repaving)             | Medium                                    | Willow Creek trail erosion is a concern.           |
| Restroom Facilities       | 3.20                                                   | Daily checks, Monthly deep clean| Q2 2025 (Upgrades for Liberty & Northwood)             | High                                      | Cleanliness inconsistent, fixtures aging.          |

**Recommendations:** Prioritize restroom upgrades and sports court resurfacing in the upcoming budget cycle. Implement a more frequent trash collection schedule for Liberty Gardens and Northwood Commons during peak season. Evaluate options for revitalizing Southside Green to increase usage.

# Laporan Penjualan Tiket Bioskop "CineMAX Lokal" - Minggu Pertama Mei 2025

Manajemen Bioskop CineMAX - Kota Hiburan

Analisis penjualan tiket dan preferensi penonton untuk film-film yang sedang tayang (1-7 Mei 2025) guna optimalisasi strategi promosi dan penjadwalan.

## Penjualan Tiket Harian Berdasarkan Judul Film (Minggu Pertama Mei 2025)

| Judul Film Tayang     | Rata-rata Penjualan Harian (Tiket) | Total Penjualan Minggu Ini (Tiket) | Studio Penayangan Utama | Estimasi Pendapatan Kotor Minggu Ini (Rp) | Rating Penonton (Internal Survey) |
|-----------------------|------------------------------------|------------------------------------|-------------------------|-------------------------------------------|-----------------------------------|
| Film_Aksi_Naga        | 195                                | 1365                               | Studio 1 & 3 (bergantian)| 54,600,000                                | 4.5/5                             |
| Film_Komedi_Kocak     | 160                                | 1120                               | Studio 2                | 44,800,000                                | 4.2/5                             |
| Film_Horor_Malam      | 220                                | 1540                               | Studio 3 & 1 (bergantian)| 61,600,000                                | 4.0/5 (peak Jumat & Sabtu malam)  |
| Film_Drama_Keluarga   | 85 (weekday matinee dominan)       | 595                                | Studio 2 (siang)        | 23,800,000                                | 4.6/5                             |
*Tabel PT1. Data penjualan mingguan dirata-ratakan dan diagregasi dari log harian. Harga tiket rata-rata Rp 40.000,-*

## Analisis Preferensi Penonton (Berdasarkan Survei Exit Poll Minggu Ini - n=250)

| Genre Film Paling Diminati | Persentase Pemilih Genre (%) | Alasan Utama Memilih Menonton di CineMAX Lokal | Kelompok Usia Penonton Dominan | Rekomendasi Promosi Lanjutan                    |
|----------------------------|------------------------------|----------------------------------------------|--------------------------------|-------------------------------------------------|
| Aksi                       | 46%                          | Kualitas Audio Dolby Atmos & Layar Besar     | 25-35 tahun                    | Paket combo tiket + merchandise film aksi.      |
| Komedi                     | 28%                          | Harga Tiket Promo & Suasana Santai           | 18-28 tahun                    | Promo "Nonton Bareng Teman" untuk film komedi.|
| Horor                      | 17%                          | Jadwal Tayang Malam & Efek Suara Mengejutkan | 17-25 tahun                    | Jadwalkan "Midnight Show" khusus film horor.   |
| Drama                      | 9%                           | Kenyamanan Studio & Pilihan Film Berkualitas | 30-45+ tahun                   | Promo khusus untuk penonton keluarga/pasangan.  |

**Strategi Pekan Depan:**

1.  Pertahankan jam tayang primetime untuk Film Horor Malam dan Film Aksi Naga.
2.  Tingkatkan promosi Film Komedi Kocak dengan penawaran grup/pelajar.
3.  Pertimbangkan penambahan sesi matinee untuk Film Drama Keluarga jika ada permintaan.
4.  Evaluasi kembali harga tiket promo untuk hari kerja (Senin-Kamis).
